<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-3135</num>
  <heading>Claims payment report.</heading>
  <text>A health insurer shall include with its annual report filed with the Commissioner a claims payment report to include the:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>Number of claims received in the previous calendar year;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>Number of claims denied in the previous calendar year;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(3)</num>
    <text>Number of claims paid:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(A)</num>
      <text>In the previous calendar year;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(B)</num>
      <text>In 30 days;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(C)</num>
      <text>In 60 days;</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(D)</num>
      <text>In 120 days; and</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(E)</num>
      <text>In more than 120 days; and</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(4)</num>
    <text>Average number of days to pay a claim submitted in the previous calendar year.</text>
  </para>
